{
  "doc_id": "36090",
  "text": "For Southern blotting 2 μg of genomic DNA from Mycobacterium were digested with ApaI or SmaI, separated by electrophoresis in a 1% agarose gel and capillary transferred to positively charged nylon membranes (GE Healthcare, Buckinghamshire, UK) by following a standard protocol [CITATION_1] . An 1818 bp region of the plasmid pYUB854 carrying the Hyg r gene was amplified using the primer pair Hyg2K FW (5´-CAC CGT ACG TCT CGA GGA ATT CCT G-3´) and Hyg2K BW (5´-GCG TCG TGA AGA AGG TGT TGC TGA-3´) and the digoxigenin labeling Kit (Roche, Mannheim Germany). The labeled PCR-product was used as a probe and detection was carried out using anti-digoxigenin-AP conjugate and CDP-star (Roche) according to the manufacturers' instructions.",
